content.detailedDescription:
I was jogging one day from ashburn to leesburg on th bike trail. it was about seven thirty at night. i was listening to music when something talked to me through my mind. it told me to look to my right. as i turned to my right i saw this bright glowing ufo and at the same time it was shining. it was hovering maybe 50 to 100 feet in the air and about the same distance away from me. as i looked at it i had stopped and took off my earphones and just stared in amazement. the ufo was hovering without moving at all and was about 100ft to 150ft in length. it was right in front of me. it only let me look at it for 3 to four seconds. then it blinked so fast it fanished streight in the deriction i was jogging. it was quick i knew it was'nt out of this world. my heart was pounding and i was scared. i was'nt sure what i saw but it was amazing.
i then jogged quicker and faster like as if i was running. i did'nt know if it was there to get me or just let me see it with my own eyes. as i ran home i then believed 100% there is other life in the universe.
content.summary: Glowing looking sphere and at the same time shining.

content.detailedDescription:
Driving north i-95 between woolbright & atlantic ave exits near delray beach, fl.

saw bright lights moving slowly east to west over i-95. thought why was a string of planes flying so low.  pulled over to shoulder and filmed them from car with cellphone.

some flew out of sight and some had had lights go out.

called my dad and mother who witnessed them from their home in boynton beach.
content.summary: Chain of lights in triangle formation

content.detailedDescription:
Driving home with my wife from a christmas dinner at my brothers we decided to look at christmas lights.  at exactly 20:30 hours i told her to pull the car over quickly.  she was unaware of what was going on until i told her to check out the orbs in the south east sky.  
the orbs were pulsating and moving at the speed of a cessna 150 which was about 120 mph. they were in a straight line.  the first 2 were about a 1/2 mile apart traveling in a straight line and no sound.  the second set were about 2 miles behind the first two heading in the same direction and about the same speed.  they started to pick up speed and the first two orbs just blinked out (vanished) and when the second set approached the same area also blinked out.  we just looked at each other and couldn't believe it happened again.  this is the third time in since september 16th that this has happened with the vanishing orbs.  we keep looking around at the sky thinking that they would maybe reappear but they never reappeared. this is becoming very concerning to the both of us.  what is going on?
content.summary: 4 orange/red orbs traveling from the north west to the south east in a straight line then blinked out and vanished again!

content.detailedDescription:
It was a very clear night, with no clouds, and the stars looked very bright.  so i went outside and took some random photographs of the sky to see if any of the pictures would come out.

i observed nothing, i saw no ufo, or lights, until i got the pictures on my computer and in about a dozen or so photos i caught a snake like ufo, that seemed to change shape and color some.

the pictures are all from different angles but clearly show the craft shape and colors.  a few stars made it in the picture, which makes a great marker for the ufo object.

i went out again about 2 hours later and took more photographs, and sure enough when i got inside i have a bunch more images of the object.

i have the original images on my camera still, i also have all the original pictures on 2 computers.  i have over a dozen images of this object.

i am only releasing one photo of the object at this time.
content.summary: After taking pictures of the stars, i found a ufo in the photos when i got them on my computer

content.detailedDescription: My son and i out on back deck facing north, saw 2 red pulsing objects, no sound, slowly flying west to east, with the trailing object slowly getting closer to lead object. unlike any airplane i've ever seen, no blinking lights, slow pulse and very red, roundish object.
content.summary: 2 red pulsing lights changed direction, then went west to east, last one slowly getting closer to lead object.

content.detailedDescription:
I would always look in the sky gazing at stars in the night or in the morning
will this one i was looking at one star as i would see a airplane with its with blinking light pass through the sky. as i was watching this one star in particular for the longest time. while my wife driving into the village in the val-court area suddenly this star i was watching descend suddenly very fast in a downward direction in the sky.With evasive action for 4 seconds then it would stop then it would make a circular motion within that time.

and after that it was all i would see i just took my eyes of it. and what affected me the most to see how fast past through the morning sky about that fast per-second. this has been the 3rd encounter that i had saw with in 2005
that i been here.
content.summary: My wife was driving about that time of morning as she was taking her son and us to her folks to stay over and spend christmas. and as i was watching this one star way up in the sky as it was on the right side of me while she was driving the car.

content.detailedDescription: My son is in hutchison prison.. he called me tonite and told me tht guards at a near by facility actually observed the crask... and then military presence... saying it was an experimental drone... it was shown on here on a flat bed trailer covered by tarps....
content.summary: Saucer crash seen by prison guards

content.detailedDescription: My son is in hutchison prison.. he called me tonite and told me tht guards at a near by facility actually observed the crask... and then military presence... saying it was an experimental drone... it was shown on here on a flat bed trailer covered by tarps....

content.detailedDescription:
I saw a yellowish to orange light that appeared star like traveling low in the sky moving east to west while driving with my wife to a friends house.It was a totally clear sky with stars. i stopped at a stop sign then we saw a second light following ,thinking they were helicopters i turned the engine on the truck off
to listen to the sound there was silence as they continued west. my wife wanted to go so i continued about a block to my friend house still watching the lights as i drove
i went in to call my friends out to see the lights.
one was still there but further away and much higher in the sky {note i was traveling east all the while}
gary and diedra saw the odd star like light immediately, it seemed to have stopped. as we watched on a commercial jet was coming in from the north at a
lower altitude, before the jet came inline with the light it started to move again, suddenly it shot to the
sky at a great speed and disappeared. brewerton ny 7:30- 8:00 pm 12-24-11
content.summary: I saw a yellowish to orange light that appeared star like traveling low in the sky moving east to west while driving with my wife to a friends hous

content.detailedDescription:
me and a buddy were having a smoke outside of my car down at the beach. suddenly over the ocean, a bright pulsating light shown bright, and seemed to change shapes never looking like a particular shape other then an odd shaped orb. it was stationary, and was white, white/blue light. larger then star but smaller then the moon. seemed far away, yet the light seemed so close. the light was very crisp and defined. there was no noise.  after about 30 seconds or so, the object shriveled up to about the size of a star, its light become more consistent like a star, and then it stared moving quite fast to the west, then seemed to go more upwards, until it faded out of sight.

  me and my fiend both agreed that the object seemed to at first be re-fueling or re-charging, being stationary and also pulsating increadably bright, until it was then able to fly off and up away from the earth.

  i have recently seen 3 very similar, and more recent clips of what looks to be the same type of object that we seen, over lake erie.
content.summary: Bright, pulsating light seemed to change shapes, then starlike.

content.detailedDescription: About 8:45pm sat.Night spotted a red to orangish light heading in straight line, we pulled of to the side of the road and watched it for about 7 min. and moved in straight line and then started hovering and changed directions about 90 degree turn and headed off and faded away into low level clouds.As we watched the object it gave us a weird feeling almost like a priminition feeling
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Bright red glowing light with a round shape with no other flashing lights,  moving slow to medium speed

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i fixed cooffe and went outside onto the patio like every other summer morning. after about 5 min. my wife said, what is that. i looked up and immediately saw what she was talking about. i didnt answer because i didnt know, she ask again. i told her i didnt know. we viewed in amazement as this round bright light with no sound disappeerd over the top of the house. there was no sound at all. i have been in around aircraft all my life. my wife and reguraly look at the stars and aircraft in the night sky. this was the first time we have never been able to identify.
i wished i had ran around the house to continue to watch the flight but i guess we were somewhat dumbfounded at the time.
content.summary: Bright white round light no sound app. 1000 ft.

content.detailedDescription: I went out side for a smoke. as always i looked up to see the stars and saw a craft flying slowly directly overhead. there was no sound, the only light was the light from the stree lights etc. reflecting off the craft. as soon as i saw it i yelled inside for my relatives to come see. the only one to get out in time was my son. he saw the craft but not in the detail i did when it was right over head. i really want to know what this thing was. this is a heavily populated area. there must have been other witnesses who also seen this.
content.summary: Viewed craft right above sister inlaws house.

content.detailedDescription: Exactly the same as a previous md entry.An orange light that was stationary.I looked away breifly.Looked back it was gone.
content.summary: Orange stationary light..I looked away breifly.When i looked back it was gone

content.detailedDescription: My brother and i were driving in troy and saw a giant craft hovering. it was around 10 15 at night. we got out of the car to watch it. it was a triangle formation with three orange balls of light. it was there for about 3 to 7 minutes and very slowly started moving east. then it was gone.
content.summary: Extremely huge, about a square mile. moving slow in the east direction then disappeared

content.detailedDescription:
We were driving down telegraph near 94, a large triangular object with lights on three corners starting to circle in an unusual pattern.  i thought it was a plane as we were 5 miles from the airport. it looked unusual to me because the lights were not flashing, it was too low in the sky and made an unusual tight turn. as i watched it came to a stop and just hovered in place.  we were driving and unable to stop immediatly to watch it on a very busy road.  we turned around the car arround and the object was gone.  

hoping that someone else saw this.
content.summary: Driving down telegraph large triangular object starting to circle and then hover in one place.  distict non pulsating lights to make up a triangle.

content.detailedDescription:
I am reporting this incident on behalf of two friends of mine that witnessed something incredibly strange last tuesday morning. i'm reporting this in the hopes that someone else may have seen this object to confirm what occurred.

from what i understand, my two friends were driving home to turner valley from calgary and as they were turning onto highway 22x from mckenzie lake blvd in the se of the city they witnessed a vibrant green orb that descended incredibly quickly at a 45 degree angle towards a park area. the object was described as having a bright green center, with a black circle around it and then another thin green ring.

my one friend is ex-military and said he had never witnessed anything remotely like it in his life and that it was a highly unusual incident to him. he said it was no way that it was neither a helicopter or a plane and that it could not have been a flare or a meteorite because of the colour and the way that it moved. the object then disappeared in a park area by the river to the north of highway 22x between deerfoot trail and mcleod trail.
content.summary: Strange descending green orb

content.detailedDescription: On the night of feb. 5, 2009 i went out to check the skies like i usually do.  directly above my house i saw 2 really big triangle light patterns. i started filming and was able to catch the second one disappearing. then 7 lights in a row appeared and then disappeared. after that one light appeared and then was gone a few moments later.  towards the end of the sighting jets started appearing from everywhere. there were at least 12 jets out possibly more. no noise from the lights at all.
content.summary: 2 really big triangle light patterns above my house.  7 lights in a row. then one light.

content.detailedDescription: The light appeared in the mountains of upstate new york in bleeker. it moved across the sky, at first resembling a star but than began to stop, hover, and the proceed moving. shortly after the sighting reports on my scanner indicated a police and military presence in the area. the light then disappeared and all was silent. moments later the sky was filled with black helicopters followed by a strong police presence in the area.
content.summary: Red light in the sky immediately followed by military air craft

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i were outside on our deck hot-tubbing around 9:30pm mst on christmas eve.  we like to star gaze and and watch planes fly overhead in the night sky.  my husband noticed a bright red light high in the sky approaching from the east.  he thought it was an airplane from the speed of its movement, but it had no sound or additional white blinking lights that we usually see on planes.  it was just a single red sphere of light.  it then stopped moving and hovered in the air.  the night sky was very clear and the stars were quite abundant, and this object looked and twinkled like another large star except it was red.  it was a very vivid red, similar to laser light.  the brightness of the color would fade some, then return to a brighter red, but in a random pattern that made it seem to pulsate.  after staying stationary for a few minutes, it then moved in a northwestern direction which seemed towards us, as the size appeared to increase.  then it stopped again, hovered and pulsated for a longer time, maybe 10 or 15 minutes.  we both were tossing around ideas what it could be, anything from a satellite, military craft from the nearby air force base, or even santa claus since it was christmas eve!  as we were discussing this, i had the feeling that it was drifting closer to us which made me feel very uncomfortable, although my husband seemed merely curious.  as we left the hot tub, we noticed the object was moving slowly again, returning towards the east where it came from.  we went into the house but continued to observe the object from the backdoor.  after another 10 minutes or so, it quickly picked up speed and flew away until we could no longer see it.  total duration of this event was roughly 35 minutes.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Moving, then hovering, bright red star-like light

content.detailedDescription: On june 22, 2009 at approximately 9:49 pm i went outside to check the skies like most nights.  i noticed something bright in the sky, so i grabbed my camcorder and started filming.  at first i could only see one slow strobing light because it was headed straight towards me.  then it made a fairly sharp turn to the left and that is when i could really see the triangle light pattern on this object.  of the three lights, only one was strobing.  after i knew i had some clear footage of it, i stopped filming briefly to set up my tripod.  it was already connected to my camcorder. i then resumed filming but by that time this object had really picked up its speed.  i could not get a steady shot even with my tripod.  it then got so far away i could not see it anymore. this object made no sound at all. really strange!
content.summary: Triangle light object with one slow strobing light.  of the three lights, only one was strobing.  abrupt turn to the north.  moved away quickly.

content.detailedDescription: My son's freind was moving his truck to the back of our house. he parked his truck and noticed a light to the west thrugh our back fence. he said the orange light moved up to and to the west pulsed and then he called us to see the light. we came out an looked to the west, did not see anything. we live in west seattle washington and live a mile east of alki point. my son and his freind keep watching to see if thay would any thing more. thay called us out of the house about two minets later. my wife and i saw this ogange glowing object, moving up to the west and we saw a jet fly toward the object (we live in the flight line to sea-tac airport) the jet flew under the object and the object seemed to move away toward the west and fade away. the strang thing we can always hear the jets but there was no sound. to the west of our house is puget sound and then bremerton navel ship yards and banger trident bases.12-24-11
content.summary: west  direction orange glow at 5000 ft moving west and out of sight

content.detailedDescription: At around 8:30pm my wife and i observed between 7 to 8 fireball like lights in the sky above northwest arkansas(springdale,ar) on dec 24th, 2011. the first light was maybe a mile or so in front of the second set of three, then a 4th and 5th and then a 6th and 7th came from the west. they traveled east for a few seconds then began to turn upwards and south and faded quickly. there are no airports in that direction and we couldn't hear anything (ie a helicopter or plane) they were low enough that had they been a plane or helicopter we should've been able to hear engine noise. they also flew in the same flight path, they were in a straight line and then the set of three split into a triangle pattern before fading away. they were all red and flew in a straight line. the objects were round but in the pictures you can't see it too well, didn't have time to set up the tripod or set the settings for night pictures. i have a video of about a minute or two that's shows them better.
content.summary: 7 fireball like lights in the sky flying west to east the south again. they came in waves so to speak, 1 then a set of three and then in 2 sets of 2.

content.detailedDescription: I went outside in my back yard and saw, in the eastern sky just above the horizon, what looked like red star. i called inside to my 13 year old daughter and had her look at it too. she saw it the same as i did. 5 minutes later my neighbor also came out and i pointed it out to him and he saw the same thing. this whole time it never moved at all. then i put a post onto facebook and while i was getting comments about it being mars or the sirius star, the red light sped off straight up just like a really fast rocket and disappeared.
content.summary: Was outside by myself when i saw what looked like a bright red slightly pulsating star

content.detailedDescription: My husband saw a light while he was in the backyard and called for my mother and i to come out and view it. it moved rapidly and can be described as a fish swimming in water. it looked like a fiber optic light moving from one color to the next seamlessly. i told him to go get a camera and by the time he came back it looked as if it landed somewhere near the west mesa. i viewed it personally for about a minute. my husband viewed it for about 2 minutes. we will never forget what we saw this christmas eve night.
content.summary: Changed colors like a fiber optic light, moved up and down, swayed side to side very rapidly

content.detailedDescription:
Two of us witnessed 5 very large bright orange lights moving from the east over our neighborhood, heading due west.  they made no sound & moved in perfect formation.  3 in a v and 2 off to the left.  moving west away from our area they seemed to climb in elevation & one by one disappeared from sight.  it was a perfectly cloudless sky.  the lights were much brighter & larger than the brightest star.  we shot video for 2 min & during that time, an incoming airplane can be seen & heard in the frame.  we called local police who arrived after the sighting, but confirmed other calls coming in from the area.

we were very shaken, as we did not believe what we witnessed.  it was extremely unsettling.  we would like to submit our video, but cannot transfer it right now. please let me know if you are interested in seeing it & we will get it onto our computer.
content.summary: 5 low flying soundless orange lights heading from east due west, raising in elevation until they disappeard

content.detailedDescription: At 730 pm on 12-24-2011 my son and i were coming home from the store and as we turned on 42nd in loveland, co. we saw three red lights hovering over the foothills all at different altitudes. they were much bigger than stars and started moving in different directions but came back close together like a triangle and hovered again.They hovered for almost a minute then faded out of sight. about fifteen seconds later either in front of or in the foothills which is about 3 miles from my house, 3 more red lights rose straight up from the ground and did basically what the first three lights did but time we watched thes three lights for 3 to 5 minutes. the lights also faded out like the other ones before. again like 15 seconds later three more lights rose straight up from the same area but this time two of the lights were really close together as they were rising and the other light was to the south like a half a mile is how far it looked. these thre rose up then hovered for a couple minutes then they rose up higher than all the rest and as they were rising they stretched out horizontally about a mile apart and proceeded to fly west over the mountains till i couldnt see the lights anymore. at that time i phoned a friend who lives only a mile from the foothills and she could see three red lights and the light that was furthest south was brighter than the other two but were definitely red. todd m. albright
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Me and my son saw sets of 3 red pulsating lights rise straight up from the ground.

content.detailedDescription: Myself and 3 others were smoking cigs after an aa mtg in the alleyway of our meeting hall when abrubtly a large orange fireball shot up into the sky.The fireball then remained stationary at about 45% looking westward. the fireball hovered and wobbled in place for about 30 seconds. the intensity was still very bright orange while it hovered in place.The object then started to slowly ascend and at the same time it's brightness decreased as it proceeded upwards until it just faded into an imperceptable point of light.
content.summary: Bright orange fireball shot up from horizon in the west,hovered then slowly ascended into space?

content.detailedDescription: About 8:40 pm while outside with my dog i was getting ready to go in to the house when i noticed what looked like an orange meteor but then realized it was not moving fast enough or burning up as i watched. it held my attention until a second one caught my peripheral vision i watch the two of the recede toward the kc area to the east when a third came from the west moving east behind the other two. i watched the three of them receding when a fourth and finally a fifth traveling in the same directions. all five were a very pretty dark glowing orange with no change in color or no apparent strobe or pulsating. i couldnt tell the distance from where i was stand but i would guess between 2 and 3 miles.  they followed one another by a separation of maybe 20 to 30 seconds. they were moving faster than a plane would have been and even though it was a cloudless starlit evening i did not see from where they came. i watched them for about 5 minutes as they disappeared toward the east. what was strange is that on such a night you can see a plane at quite a distance and hear its drone. these objects seem to appear as i was watching the others out of the south west somewhere. they were bright enough and attractive enough that they would have been noticed following one another had they been in some sort of formation but they were not. each on caught my attention separately and totally by surprise as i was watching the others. too cool!
content.summary: Five glowing orange objects flying in single file from lenexa, kansas toward kansas city

content.detailedDescription: I was taking my girlfriend and her son home. we had just came acroos a bridge and made a left hand turn. i saw something out of the corner of my eye and turned my head to look. off to my left in the sky was an extremely bright white light. the color was what you would think of if someone said something was "white hot". it had around it a dimmer reddish light. it moved very fast and either flew or fell beyond the trees that made up the horizon. i had no idea what it could be, because i've seen aircraft of all types flying low at night. this had none of the identifying lights of a normal aircraft. i also have never seen an aircraft move with that much speed. i just kept racking my brain for any ordinary explanation and couldn't come up with one. it happened in a matter of seconds. my girlfriend also saw it.
content.summary: White light surrounded by a much dimmer red light
